page.title: 11Wild Life
page.content: There is alot of wild life in this area not just trees,insects,and animals but birds.There were sixteen different species of birds that we saw on a walk around the school run.For example Black Birds,Blue tits,Great tits,Chaffinch,Magpie and many more. The area is a haven for all types of water fowl and is protected by conservationists.The local rivers and dykes are well stocked with fish and are used by various angling clubs.In the hedgerows a visitor could expect to see a wide variety of wildlife.
